com.github.dm.jrt.android.v4.stream

Interface LoaderStreamBuilderCompat<IN,OUT>

  • Type Parameters:
    IN - the input data type.
    OUT - the output data type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    InvocationConfigurable<RoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>>, InvocationConfiguration.Configurable<RoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>>, LoaderConfigurable<LoaderStreamBuilderCompat<IN,OUT>>, LoaderConfiguration.Configurable<LoaderStreamBuilderCompat<IN,OUT>>, Routine<IN,OUT>, RoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>, StreamBuilder<IN,OUT>

    public interface LoaderStreamBuilderCompat<IN,OUT>
extends StreamBuilder<IN,OUT>, LoaderConfigurable<LoaderStreamBuilderCompat<IN,OUT>>
    Interface defining a builder of routines concatenating map and reduce functions.
    Each function in the stream will be backed by a routine instance, which may have its own specific configuration and invocation mode.
    In order to prevent undesired leaks, the class of the specified functions must have a static scope.

    Note that, if at least one reduce function is part of the chain, the results will be propagated only when the built routine invocation completes.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 07/04/2016.

LoaderConfiguration.Builder<? extends LoaderStreamBuilderCompat<IN,OUT>> applyStreamLoaderConfiguration()
        Gets the Loader configuration builder related to the whole stream.

        Throws:

      • on

        @NotNull
LoaderStreamBuilderCompat<IN,OUT> on(@Nullable
                                              LoaderContextCompat context)
        Sets the stream Loader context.
        The context will be used by all the concatenated routines until changed.
        If null it will cause the next routines to employ the configured runner instead of an Android Loader.
        Parameters:
        context - the Loader context.
        Returns:
        the new stream instance.
